  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>steak[s]</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> and dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coconut flakes</strong> roughly and chop your<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583502049039-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583502049039-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583502049039-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583502049039-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583502049039-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>diced tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped coconut flakes</strong>, and <strong>chopped parsley</strong> with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1/4 of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>red onion</strong> (save the rest for later!) in a bowl</p><p>Add the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>coconut sambal</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583502053088-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583502053088-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583502053088-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583502053088-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583502053088-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the <strong>outer green pods</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>,<strong> curry powder</strong>, <strong>black mustard seeds</strong>, and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583502057788-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583502057788-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583502057788-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583502057788-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583502057788-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, transfer to a small bowl and set aside for later – this is your <strong>toasted curry powder</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> basmati rice </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583502062907-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583502062907-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583502062907-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583502062907-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583502062907-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583502066703-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583502066703-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583502066703-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583502066703-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583502066703-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>pork loin steak[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper, then trim the fat and discard</p><p>Chop the <strong>pork loin steak[s] </strong>into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the onion has softened, increase the heat to high and add the <strong>chopped pork </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for 5-6 min or until the pork is beginning to brown all over</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583502070865-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583502070865-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583502070865-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583502070865-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583502070865-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and the <strong>toasted curry powder</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add your<strong> tamarind paste</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>water</strong>, 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and the juice of the <strong>remaining lime</strong> and cook for 5-6 min further or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Sri Lankan-style pork curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583502078482-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583502078482-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583502078482-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583502078482-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583502078482-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Season the <strong>Sri Lankan-style pork curry</strong> with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Serve the <strong>Sri Lankan-style pork curry</strong> over the<strong> basmati rice</strong> with the <strong>coconut sambal</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
